  "notes": "Single shared data artifact for ALGORITHM v4. Python and TypeScript MUST load tables from this file (vendored by content hash), never restate them in code. Additions are a CHECKS_VERSION bump with regenerated fixtures, justified by calibration-corpus measurement. definitive_v1/hedge_v1 are the EXACT v0 lists from sanna-repo receipt.py (ground truth); multi-word entries match as folded token sequences; '100%' matches via the PCT100 tokenizer rule. Round-20: negative benefit words are deny_triggers (explicit polarity; the NEG_v1 XOR deny rule makes 'nonrefundable' a NEG-polarity refund_availability frame); generic benefit normalization applies to BOTH polarities; contractions expand at tokenization and table entries are matched post-expansion. Round-21: Dec = {coefficient: signed BigInt, scale: nonneg int} with canonical trailing-zero removal; MAX_DEC_DIGITS/MAX_DEC_SCALE bound representation; comparators_v1 maps comparator token sequences to intervals over the parsed value v (null bound = unbounded); a bare scalar is [v, v]. Round-22: units_v1 flattened to token -> {group, factor}; concept_v1 normalizes condition-atom tokens (post-stem) to canonical concept forms so 'requires approval' and 'if approved' share the atom {approval} -- applied only inside Bool atoms, never extent terms.",
